OL,3,C'I was forced to do so' ` alleged
OL,4,CChannel small boat pilot tells court
OL,6,FAccording to the Home Office, the
OL,7,Fcharge of endangering others during a
OL,8,Fsea crossing is to stop more people
OL,9,Fbeing crammed into unsafe boats and
OL,10,Fwould apply to those involved in
OL,11,Fphysical aggression and intimidation,
OL,12,Fas well as anyone who resists rescue.
OL,14,FWhen the plans for the offence were
OL,15,Ffirst announced last January, Home
OL,16,FOffice sources said there had been
OL,17,Finstances of "floating crime scenes"
OL,18,Fwhere people had acted in such a
OL,19,Freckless way people died on board in
OL,20,Fcrushes and drownings.
